{"author":{"id":"cff9ab1d2ee9741039b2a60d90cca378a5320ba753398f6f3df8d03abcebee1b"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1771943016,"nonce":"Mkhe1AieJNnTI7mHdnCVWZ4sb2M=","title":"Seed users for every role","message":"Currently only a single admin user (admin@example.com) is seeded. We should seed one user per department membership role so every role can be tested during development.\n\nRoles to seed (from DepartmentMembership enum):\n- guest\n- member\n- leader\n\nPlus the admin flag on User.\n\nEach seeded user should follow the pattern:\n- Email: \u003crole\u003e@example.com (e.g. guest@example.com, member@example.com, leader@example.com)\n- Password: same as existing seed user (platypus-umbrella-cactus)\n- Firstname/Lastname derived from the role for easy identification\n\nThe existing admin@example.com user already covers admin+leader. We need at minimum:\n- member@example.com (role: member, admin: false)\n- guest@example.com (role: guest, admin: false)\n\nHidden and deleted are system states, not real user roles - skip those unless needed.","files":null}]}